        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41507",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=iosart",
                        "name": "iosart",
                        "displayName": "Alex Sirota",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Looked further into this issue and it seams to go a bit deeper than the assertHeaderContains function itself.\r\nThe sendHeaders method of Zend_Controller_Response_HttpTestCase assumes that there's only one header with a given name in the response:\r\n        foreach ($this->_headers as $header) {\r\n            $name = $header['name'];\r\n            $key  = strtolower($name);\r\n            if (array_key_exists($name, $headers)) {\r\n                if ($header['replace']) {\r\n                    $headers[$key] = $header['name'] . ': ' . $header['value'];\r\n                }\r\n            } else {\r\n                $headers[$key] = $header['name'] . ': ' . $header['value'];\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n\r\nSo, if 'replace' is true, the second instance will be used, but if it's false, the first instance is used, rather then *both instances* of the header, which would be the correct behavior. \r\n\r\nBTW, the real Zend_Controller_Response_Abstract class does not have this bug, as it correctly uses the 'header' function, that would output multiple headers of the same type, if 'replace' is 'false':\r\n       foreach ($this->_headers as $header) {\r\n            if (!$httpCodeSent && $this->_httpResponseCode) {\r\n                header($header['name'] . ': ' . $header['value'], $header['replace'], $this->_httpResponseCode);\r\n                $httpCodeSent = true;\r\n            } else {\r\n                header($header['name'] . ': ' . $header['value'], $header['replace']);\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n\r\nAs this looks like a major bug in Zend_Test, bumping the ticket from 'enhancement' to 'bug'\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=iosart",
                        "name": "iosart",
                        "displayName": "Alex Sirota",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-16T01:32:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-16T01:32:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41512",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=iosart",
                        "name": "iosart",
                        "displayName": "Alex Sirota",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Attaching a proposed fix (sorry for not creating a proper patch, didn't have time to tweak all the affected places under Zend_Test_*\r\n\r\nThe proposed fix:\r\n\r\n1) in Zend_Controller_Response_HttpTestCase::sendHeaders \r\n   * when $header['replace'] is false, instead of ignoring the header, the entry $headers[$key] becomes an array instead of a string\r\n   * also, there seems to be a bug in the main 'if':\r\n      if (array_key_exists($name, $headers)) \r\n     should be\r\n      if (array_key_exists($key, $headers)) \r\n\r\n2) in Zend_Test_PHPUnit_Constraint_ResponseHeader::_headerRegex and similar methods\r\n    * call $this->_getHeader as usual to find the header entry\r\n    * if a scalar is returned (current functionality), just treat as today\r\n    * if an array is returned (this fix), go over all the elements of the returned array and try to match against each one\r\n\r\nHope all this makes sense :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=iosart",
                        "name": "iosart",
                        "displayName": "Alex Sirota",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-16T02:27:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-16T02:27:14.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
